OK in my case, X11/Xlib.h file defines Status to int. But TensorFlow also has a Status class which conflicts with the define macro.

I undefined the Status (using #undef Status) which solved the problem for me.

body:
OK in my case, X11/Xlib.h file defines Status to int. But TensorFlow also has a Status class which conflicts with the define macro. 

I undefined the Status (using #undef Status) which solved the problem for me.
